<paragraph id="A44DAF3E9D41FFEBFEDEFEB7FE47FE9F" blockId="5.[264,894,283,345]" box="[264,384,319,345]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
<figureCitation id="3CC9B3BB9D41FFEBFEDEFEB7FE47FE9F" box="[264,384,319,345]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 11" captionStartId="6.[264,382,1572,1596]" captionTargetBox="[289,1292,456,1527]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[267,1321,449,1546]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 11. Pygommatius apoticius Scarbrough, terminalia. Male, 1 – 3. Lateral, dorsal, and ventral views; 4. Hypandrial bristle with bracts; 5. Epandrium with three branches, dorsal view; 6. Gonostylus, lateral view; 7. Aedeagus, lateral view. Female, 8 – 9. Dorsal and ventral views; 10. Spermatheca; 11. Genital fork. Abbrevations: Ae = aedeagus; AS = aedeagal sheath; Ce = cercus; E p = epandrium; Ej = ejaculatory apodeme; DB = dorsal branch of epandrium; MB = middle branch of epandrium; VB = ventral branch of epandrium; DA = dorsal and VA = ventral apodemes of aedeagal sheath; Gc = gonocoxite; Gs = gonostylus; Hp = hypandrium; T = moundlike tubercle; St 8 = sternite 8; T 8 = tergite 8; T 9 = tergite 9." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/170083/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="6">
Figs. 
<number id="123ABD199D41FFEBFE9FFEB7FE47FE9F" box="[329,384,319,345]" pageId="5" pageNumber="6" value="6.0" valueMax="11.0" valueMin="1.0">1–11</number>
</figureCitation>
</paragraph>
